The paper discusses a video codec that takes perceptual aspects into account, which suggests that it may fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) categories. Additionally, the paper mentions optimizing for metrics like PSNR, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of alternative approaches to traditional video codecs, which could also fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Signal Processing (cs.SP) categories, but these seem less likely based on the content of the abstract.
